org.micromanager.propertymap

Interface MutablePropertyMapView


  • public interface MutablePropertyMapView
    An interface to a property-map-like object that can be modified.

    TODO: This should have two superinterfaces, one shared with PropertyMap and another shared with PropertyMap.Builder.

    • Method Detail

      • keySet

        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> keySet()
        Return a set view of all of the keys in this view.

        The returned view is updated when this MutablePropertyMapView changes. Removing keys from the returned set view will remove those keys from the MutablePropertyMapView. Adding keys is not supported.

        Returns:
        set view of property keys

      • getValueTypeForKey

        java.lang.Class<?> getValueTypeForKey(java.lang.String key)
        Return a class indicating the type of the value for the given key.

        Intended for use by special library/framework code. See the analogous PropertyMap.getValueTypeForKey(java.lang.String) for details.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the class representing the type of the value stored for key
        Throws:
